All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Alliance
an enumeration that represents the alliances in a chess game; the White and Black alliances.
Bishop
The Bishop class represents a bishop chess piece.
BlackPlayer
The `BlackPlayer` class extends `Player` to represent a player controlling the black pieces in a chess game.
Board
The Board class represents a chess board containing 64 tiles and thirty-two pieces at the start of the game.
Board.Builder
A builder class for constructing instances of the Board class with specific configurations.
BoardEvaluator
 
BoardTransition
The `BoardTransition` class represents the result of a move on the chessboard.
BoardUtils
The BoardUtils class provides methods for checking valid tile coordinates and converting between positions and coordinates.
DebugPanel
Represents a panel for displaying debug information or messages.
engineDriver
The main client for the chessEngine package.
GameHistoryPanel
Represents a panel that displays the move history of the game in a table format.
GameSetup
The `GameSetup` class represents a dialog for configuring game setup options using Java Swing.
King
The King class represents a king chess piece.
KingSafetyAnalyzer
The `KingSafetyAnalyzer` class is responsible for analyzing the safety of the king during a chess game.
KingSafetyAnalyzer.KingDistance
The `KingDistance` class represents the distance between the player's king and the closest enemy piece.
Knight
The Knight class represents a knight chess piece.
Move
The Move class represents a chess move within the chess engine.
Move.AttackMove
The `AttackMove` class represents a move that results in attacking an opponent's piece in chess.
Move.CastleMove
The `CastleMove` class represents a move that involves castling, which is a special king and rook move.
Move.KingSideCastleMove
The `KingSideCastleMove` class represents a move for king-side castling in chess.
Move.MajorAttackMove
The `MajorAttackMove` class represents a major attack move in chess.
Move.MajorMove
The `MajorMove` class represents a standard major move in chess.
Move.MoveFactory
Represents a factory for creating moves.
Move.MoveStatus
Represents the possible outcomes of a chess move, including successful execution, an illegal move, or leaving the player's king in check.
Move.NullMove
The `NullMove` class represents a placeholder for no move in a chess game.
Move.PawnAttackMove
The `PawnAttackMove` class represents a pawn attack move in chess.
Move.PawnEnPassantAttack
The `PawnEnPassantAttack` class represents a special pawn attack move called "en passant" in chess.
Move.PawnJump
The `PawnJump` class represents a pawn move where a pawn advances two squares from its starting position.
Move.PawnMove
The `PawnMove` class represents a basic pawn move in chess.
Move.PawnPromotion
The `PawnPromotion` class represents a special move in chess.
Move.QueenSideCastleMove
The `QueenSideCastleMove` class represents a move for queen-side castling in chess.
MoveStatus
The MoveStatus enum represents the possible results of a chess move execution.
MoveStrategy
 
MoveTransition
The `MoveTransition` class represents a transition between two chess board states resulting from a specific move.
MoveUtils
The `MoveUtils` class is a utility class that provides various helper methods related to chess moves and calculations.
MoveUtils.Line
The Line class represents a sequence of integer coordinates forming a line.
Pawn
The `Pawn` class represents a pawn chess piece.
PawnStructureAnalyzer
 
Piece
The Piece class represents a chess piece on the board.
Piece.PieceType
The PieceType enum defines the types of chess pieces and their associated values.
PieceUtils
The PieceUtils class is a utility class that provides methods for creating and accessing all possible moved instances of different types of chess pieces.
Player
The `Player` class is an abstract class representing a player in a chess game.
Queen
The Queen class represents a queen chess piece.
Rook
The Rook class represents a rook chess piece.
RookStructureAnalyzer
The RookStructureAnalyzer class is responsible for analyzing the rook structure on the chess board, calculating bonuses based on open files for rooks, and providing a score for rook-related factors.
StandardBoardEvaluator
The StandardBoardEvaluator class is responsible for evaluating the current state of a chess board using a standard scoring system.
StockAlphaBeta
The `StockAlphaBeta` class represents a chess engine that uses the alpha-beta search algorithm with various enhancements to determine the best move for a given chess position.
StockAlphaBeta.MoveSorter
Enumeration representing different move sorting strategies.
Table
The Table class represents the main user interface for the Capstone chess engine.
Table.AIThinkTank
An asynchronous worker class responsible for AI move calculation and execution.
Table.BoardDirection
An enumeration representing the two possible directions of the chess board display.
Table.MoveLog
A class representing a log of moves made during a chess game.
Table.PlayerType
An enumeration representing the types of players in the chess game: Human and Computer.
Table.TableGameAIWatcher
A watcher class that observes changes in the game state and triggers AI actions or displays game-over messages based on certain conditions.
Tile
The `Tile` class represents a tile on a chess board.
Tile.EmptyTile
The EmptyTile class represents an empty tile on a chess board.
Tile.OccupiedTile
The OccupiedTile class represents an occupied tile on a chess board.
WhitePlayer
The `WhitePlayer` class extends `Player` to represent a player controlling the white pieces in a chess game.
